 First, we need to calculate the total distance she can drive on the current tank of gas. Since she has already driven 100 miles and needs 4 gallons of gas to fill the tank, the total distance she can drive is equal to the amount of gas she needs. 
 \text{Distance} = \text{Gas needed} 
