 First, we need to calculate the total number of rotations for one month and then multiply it by 12 to get the total rotations for a year. Since the car drives 400 miles a month, in a year it will drive 400,000 miles. The tires rotate 725 times a month. To find the total rotations in a year, we multiply the rotations per month by 12 \text{Total rotations in a year} = 725 \text{ rotations/month} \times 12 \text{ months/year} 
