Next, we need to find out how many days it takes her to drink 16 cups of water. We divide 16 by 8 to get the number of days she drinks 8 cups per day, which is 2 days. Then, we multiply 2 days by 24 hours to get the total hours she drinks 8 cups per day. 
 \text{Total hours} = 2 \text{ days} \times 24 \text{ hours/day} = 48 \text{ hours} 
Finally, we multiply the total hours by the number of cups she drinks in a day to get the total cups she drinks in 30 days. 
 \text{Total cups} = 192 \text{ cups/day} \times 30 \text{ days} = 5700 \text{ cups} 
Therefore, Ingrid drinks 5700 cups of water in 30 days.
The answer is: 5700

 First, we need to calculate the total number of tiles needed for the floor. Since each tile is 1ft long and the floor area is 200 SqFt, we can calculate the total number of tiles as follows \text{Total tiles} = \frac{\text{Total area}}{\text{Length of each tile}} 
 \text{Total tiles} = \frac{200 \text{ ft}^2}{1 \text{ ft}} 
 \text{Total tiles} = 200 \text{ tiles} 
Since each tile costs $12, the total cost will be \text{Total cost} = \text{Number of tiles} \times \text{Cost per tile} 
 \text{Total cost} = 200 \text{ tiles} \times \$12/\text{tile} 
 \text{Total cost} = \$2400 
Therefore, it will cost me $2400 to renovate my kitchen floor.
The answer is: $2400

